article.headline: UCF 81, Bethune-Cookman 46
article.story: ORLANDO, Fla. (AP) -- Chip Cartwright scored 12 points to lead Central Florida to a 81-46 victory over Bethune-Cookman Tuesday. Central Florida (3-0) started the game on an 8-0 run and never lost the lead. The team led by 22 points in the first half. Jermaine Taylor came off Central Florida's bench to reach double figures for the third-straight game. Taylor and Josh Peppers each finished with 11 points. Peppers scored 10 of his points in the first half as Central Florida built a 41-22 advantage at the break. Jimmy Hudson led Bethune-Cookman (1-1) with 14 points. Central Florida shot for 49.1 percent, while Bethune-Cookman made 30 percent of their field goal attempts. Central Florida made 76.7 percent of their free-throws and Bethune-Cookman made 45 percent.
